    <stitle>HEAT VENTILATION AIR CONDITIONING (HVAC) SYSTEM - ProStar - REMOVE AND INSTALL - PRESSURE TRANSDUCER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl160390801" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>PRESSURE TRANSDUCER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>The pressure transducer is not interchangeable with a pressure switch. To prevent damage to
                        the A/C system replace a defective transducer only with the recommended part.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>The pressure transducer can be removed and installed without removing the refrigerant from the
                        A/C system.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1603924">Figure 24</hotlnk>
                        while performing the following Remove and Install procedures.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>The pressure transducer is located on the condenser-to-evaporator refrigerant line.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connection to pressure transducer (2, Figure 24).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unscrew pressure transducer from condenser-to-evaporator refrigerant line and cap open
                    fitting.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603924" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603924.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. A/C Condenser and Pressure Transducer</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CONDENSER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PRESSURE TRANSDUCER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SERVICE PORT (HIGH SIDE)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring on transducer fitting and lubricate O-ring and threads with
                    mineral-based oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Screw pressure transducer onto A/C line fitting and tighten to 6.8 to 13.6 N&#8226;m. (5
                    to 10 lbf-ft).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connector to pressure transducer (2).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
